HEADWORD: Pernoctation
<hw>Per`noc*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pernoctatio</ets>, fr. <ets>pernoctare</ets> to stay all night;
<ets>per</ets> + <ets>nox</ets>, <ets>noctis</ets>, night.]</ety>
<def>The act or state of passing the whole night; a remaining all
night.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pernoctation</xex> in prayer.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

